text_raw:
1. This Order may be cited as the Courts and Court Officers Act 1995 

(Section 9(2)) Order 2021.

title: the efficient transaction of business in that Court, it is necessary in the interests
heading: 2. The number of ordinary judges of the High Court otherwise provided for
text_raw:
2. The number of ordinary judges of the High Court otherwise provided for 

under any enactment for the time being in force may be exceeded by one. 

Notice of the making of this Statutory Instrument was published in 
“Iris Oifigiúil” of 10th December, 2021. 

 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 [778] 3 

GIVEN under the Official Seal of the Government, 

7 December, 2021. 

MICHEÁL MARTIN, 

Taoiseach.

text_raw:
EXPLANATORY NOTE 

(This note is not part of the Instrument and does not purport to be a legal 
interpretation.) 

This Order provides that the number of ordinary judges of the High Court 
otherwise provided for under any enactment for the time being in force may be 
exceeded by one.
